<TITLE> Bomb scare at CMC halts classes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 16 (bdnews24.com) A bomb scare halted classes and administrative work at Chittagong Medical College until midday on Sunday. Residents of area around the college also panicked on the rumours that a bomb had been planted at the college's academic building. But no bombs were discovered in a search by the police and Rapid Action Battalion. The vice chancellor's personal assistant Monowar Hossain received the bomb threat from an unidentified caller around 9.15am. VC Professor Selim Md Jahangir told bdnews24.com, "We informed the police and RAB immediately after receiving the bomb threat." Panchlaish police chief Nabajyoti Khisha told bdnews24.com that a bomb-defusing squad of RAB, Police conducted a two-hour search. "However, nothing was found anywhere. But we are still looking into the matter," he added. He also said that additional police have been deployed on the college campus. The VC said the situation had returned to normal and classes resumed at some of the faculties. bdnews
